ChatGPT said:

Ah! now it‚Äôs clear ‚Äî you want two separate pages (Login and SignUp) and when a user clicks ‚ÄúSign Up‚Äù on the login page, it navigates to the SignUp page. In React, the clean way to do this is using React Router.

Here‚Äôs a complete setup:
1. Install React Router

In your project folder:

npm install react-router-dom

2. Set up the router in App.js

// src/App.js
import React from "react";
import { BrowserRouter as Router, Routes, Route } from "react-router-dom";
import Login from "./Login";
import SignUp from "./SignUp";

function App() {
  return (
    <Router>
      <Routes>
        <Route path="/" element={<Login />} />
        <Route path="/signup" element={<SignUp />} />
      </Routes>
    </Router>
  );
}

export default App;

    / ‚Üí Login page

    /signup ‚Üí Sign Up page

3. Update Login.js to navigate to Sign Up

