in home page how would we say ok login will be upside and with this button with link for its component
ChatGPT said:

Ah, now I understand ‚Äî you want the Home page to show a ‚ÄúLogin‚Äù section at the top with a button that either opens the Login component or navigates to it. Since you don‚Äôt want routing, you can do it with state and conditional rendering in the Home page.

Here‚Äôs a clean way to handle it:
1. HomePage.js (Show Login when button clicked)

// src/components/HomePage.js
import React, { useState } from "react";
import Login from "./Login";
import SignUp from "./SignUp";
import Books from "./Books";
import "./HomePage.css";

const HomePage = () => {
  const [showLogin, setShowLogin] = useState(false); // controls login visibility
  const [showSignUp, setShowSignUp] = useState(false); // controls signup visibility

  return (
    <div className="homepage-wrapper">
      {/* Buttons to open forms */}
      <div className="top-buttons">
        <button onClick={() => { setShowLogin(true); setShowSignUp(false); }}>
          Login
        </button>
        <button onClick={() => { setShowSignUp(true); setShowLogin(false); }}>
          Sign Up
        </button>
      </div>

      {/* Render forms conditionally */}
      <div className="forms-container">
        {showLogin && <Login />}
        {showSignUp && <SignUp />}
      </div>

      {/* Books component is always visible */}
      <div className="books-container">
        <Books />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default HomePage;

2. HomePage.css Example

.homepage-wrapper {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 20px;
}

.top-buttons {
  margin-bottom: 30px;
  display: flex;
  gap: 20px;
}

.top-buttons button {
  padding: 10px 20px;
  font-size: 16px;
  border-radius: 5px;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  background-color: #d4a373; /* brown accent */
  color: #333;
  font-weight: bold;
  transition: 0.3s;
}

.top-buttons button:hover {
  background-color: #c08c5a;
}

.forms-container {
  margin-bottom: 40px;
}

.books-container {
  width: 80%;
}

‚úÖ How it works

    At first, Login and Sign Up forms are hidden.

    Clicking Login button shows the Login component.

    Clicking Sign Up button shows the Sign Up component.

    You can toggle between them easily.

    Books component stays visible all the time.

üí° Tip:
If you want, you can later make it so forms appear in a modal or slide down from the top, giving a more polished library website look.

