‚úÖ Explanation

    Current behavior:

        It does nothing with the input data.

        It just calls onSignUp() which in HomePage sets isLoggedIn = true.

        This is only to simulate a successful signup so the Profile component becomes visible.

    What it should eventually do (after backend is ready):

const handleSignUp = async () => {
  try {
    // Send the form data to your backend API
    const response = await fetch("/api/signup", {
      method: "POST",
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      body: JSON.stringify({ username, password, address })
    });

    if (response.ok) {
      // Signup succeeded
      onSignUp(); // now the user is considered logged in
    } else {
      // Handle errors (username exists, weak password, etc.)
      const errorData = await response.json();
      alert(errorData.message || "Signup failed");
    }
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Signup error:", err);
  }
};

üîπ Summary

    Current version: placeholder, does nothing except mark the user as logged in.

    Future version: send data to backend, handle success/failure, then call onSignUp() if successful.

