i want you to put login and sign up and profile in homepage SUCH that they are buttons themselves in the upside of the homepage like any web site normallly and the books under them 
ChatGPT said:

Ah! Got it ‚Äî you want a normal web portal-style homepage, where at the top of the page there are buttons for Login, SignUp, and Profile, and clicking them toggles their respective forms. Below these buttons, the Books section is always visible.

We can do this without routing, using a single state to track which form is visible.
‚úÖ HomePage.js

// src/components/HomePage/HomePage.js
import React, { useState } from "react";
import Login from "../Login/Login";
import SignUp from "../SignUp/SignUp";
import Profile from "../Profile/Profile";
import Books from "../Books/Books";
import "./HomePage.css";

const HomePage = () => {
  const [activeForm, setActiveForm] = useState(null); // 'login', 'signup', 'profile'

  return (
    <div className="homepage-wrapper">

      {/* TOP BUTTONS */}
      <header className="homepage-header">
        <button onClick={() => setActiveForm("login")}>Login</button>
        <button onClick={() => setActiveForm("signup")}>Sign Up</button>
        <button onClick={() => setActiveForm("profile")}>Profile</button>
      </header>

      {/* FORMS/PROFILE */}
      <div className="form-container">
        {activeForm === "login" && <Login />}
        {activeForm === "signup" && <SignUp />}
        {activeForm === "profile" && <Profile />}
      </div>

      {/* BOOKS ALWAYS VISIBLE */}
      <main className="homepage-main">
        <Books />
      </main>
    </div>
  );
};

export default HomePage;

‚úÖ HomePage.css

.homepage-wrapper {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  min-height: 100vh;
  background-color: #f3e9dc;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

/* TOP BUTTON BAR */
.homepage-header {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: 15px;
  padding: 15px;
  background-color: #8b5e3c;
}

.homepage-header button {
  padding: 10px 20px;
  background-color: #d4a373;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  font-weight: bold;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: 0.3s;
}

.homepage-header button:hover {
  background-color: #c08c5a;
  color: white;
}

/* FORM CONTAINER */
.form-container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  margin: 20px 0;
}

/* BOOKS SECTION */
.homepage-main {
  flex: 1;
  padding: 20px;
}

‚úÖ How it works

    Top buttons:

        Login | SignUp | Profile

        Clicking a button sets activeForm state ‚Üí shows the corresponding form in the form-container.

    Form container:

        Only the selected form is visible.

        Forms appear centered under the buttons.

    Books section:

        Always visible below the forms.

